    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const job = $input.item.json;\n\nconst positiveFeedback = '';\nconst negativeFeedback = '';\n\nconst MY_RESUME = `\nNAME: Md. Aman Uddin Siyam\n\nEDUCATION:\nBSc in Computer Science & Engineering — IUBAT, Dhaka, Bangladesh (2022 - Present)\nCGPA: 3.24\n\nSKILLS:\nAI & ML: Python, PyTorch, TensorFlow, scikit-learn, NumPy, Pandas, OpenCV, LangChain, LlamaIndex\nLLMs & RAG: Llama 3, Groq, Qdrant (Vector DB), RAG Architectures, SHAP (XAI)\nMLOps: Docker, FastAPI, Flask, GitHub Actions (CI/CD), Weights & Biases\nFull Stack: React, Next.js 14, Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB, TypeScript\nResearch: Signal Processing, EDA, Feature Engineering, Few-Shot Learning, Edge AI\n\nPROJECTS:\n1. BAT-Track — Lightweight UAV object tracking, 39.3 FPS, 60.5% power reduction, 64.2% IoU accuracy.\n2. Financial RAG Analyst — Production RAG pipeline, LlamaIndex + Qdrant + Llama 3, SEC 10-K analysis, Dockerized.\n3. DebateArena — Real-time AI-judged debate platform, Socket.IO, Gemini API, Next.js 14 + Express.js.\n4. Edge-ViT-FSL — Few-shot plant disease diagnosis, under 10MB, 22.13 FPS, 73.93% cross-domain accuracy.\n5. PCOS Detection — XGBoost+LightGBM+CatBoost ensemble, AUROC 0.976.\n\nPUBLICATIONS:\n- Voice-Based Parkinson's Disease Detection (SVM & XGBoost)\n- Clinical vs. Ultrasound for PCOS Detection (Accepted ICCIT)\n- Cosmetic Chemical Carcinogenicity ML Pipeline (Accepted ICCIT)\n- LENS-Guard: Lightweight VAE-CNN for Threat Detection (Accepted ICECTE)\n`;\n\nconst fewShotSection = (positiveFeedback || negativeFeedback) ? `\nLEARNING FROM PAST OUTCOMES:\n${positiveFeedback ? `Jobs that led to interviews/offers (score these types HIGHER):\\n${positiveFeedback}` : ''}\n${negativeFeedback ? `Jobs that led to rejections (score these types LOWER):\\n${negativeFeedback}` : ''}\nUse these patterns to calibrate your scoring.\n` : '';\n\nconst prompt = `You are a job-fit analyzer for ML/AI roles. The candidate is a final-year CS student from Bangladesh with strong ML, edge AI, RAG, and full-stack experience, plus published research.\n\nCANDIDATE RESUME:\n${MY_RESUME}\n${fewShotSection}\nJOB POSTING:\nTitle: ${job.title}\nCompany: ${job.company}\nLocation: ${job.location}\nTags: ${job.tags}\nDescription:\n${job.description}\n\nAnalyze the fit carefully. Consider that the candidate is a student — don't penalize for lack of industry experience if skills match.\n\nUse these STRICT recommendation rules based on score:\n- score 80-100 → recommendation: \"apply\"\n- score 60-79 → recommendation: \"stretch\"\n- score 0-59 → recommendation: \"skip\"\n\nDo NOT override these rules. The recommendation must match the score range exactly.\n\nRespond ONLY with valid JSON. No markdown, no text outside the JSON:\n{\n  \"score\": <integer 0-100>,\n  \"recommendation\": \"<apply|stretch|skip>\",\n  \"match_reasons\": [\"<reason1>\", \"<reason2>\", \"<reason3>\"],\n  \"missing_skills\": [\"<skill1>\", \"<skill2>\"],\n  \"one_line_summary\": \"<one sentence on fit>\"\n}`;\n\nconst requestBody = {\n  model: \"llama-3.1-8b-instant\",\n  temperature: 0.3,\n  max_tokens: 500,\n  messages: [\n    {\n      role: \"user\",\n      content: prompt\n    }\n  ]\n};\n\nreturn [{ json: {\n  requestBody,\n  stored_job_id: job.job_id,\n  stored_title: job.title,\n  stored_company: job.company,\n  stored_url: job.url,\n  stored_source: job.source,\n  stored_score: job.score,\n  stored_recommendation: job.recommendation,\n  stored_match_reasons: job.match_reasons,\n  stored_missing_skills: job.missing_skills,\n  stored_one_line_summary: job.one_line_summary\n} }];"
      },
